Only Ben Carson generates about the same level of enthusiasm as Trump (43 percent of people said they would be "enthusiastic" versus 40 percent who say the same about Trump).
Next closest to enthusiasm level?
Marco Rubio with only 21 percent.
On the other hand, 47 percent of Republican voters say they would be "displeased" or "upset" if corporate favorite Jeb Bush were to run.
Most Republicans don't see Trump's temperament as the problem.
