Yet it appears that a number of GOP voters see Trump's campaign as credible.
Even though the Republicans rallied around another candidate, Trump still beats almost everyone.
Some scholars point out that the fragmented field likely contributes to Trump's leadership, while anti-Trump support is diffuse among more than a dozen other candidates.
