Industry Minister Jan Mládek (ČSSD) told the deputies that the municipalities will get annually instead of 14 million to 100 million crowns.
The amount of mining fees will no longer be determined by law, but by government regulation.
The compensation shall be recalculated as a factor of the quantity of ore extracted and the rate for each type of ore.
According to the Government, the reason for the change is, among other things, the possibility of a flexible response to the current economic situation.
However, ODS MP Marek Benda warned that setting a fee by government regulation may not be in line with the constitution.
According to Minister Mládek, however, there is no tax in this case, as the State charges the mineral, which is state property.
