Apple has a yo-yo effect.
It's all the displays.
A more powerful processor, a higher-resolution camera, a sturdier chassis, or a touchscreen, these are, in short, the advantages of the recently introduced ninth-generation iPhones.
The latter two also have a negative impact on the size and weight of the iPhone 6s and 6s Plus.
Because Apple's trend so far has been that each new generation of iPhone is lighter than the previous one.
The only exception was the third and fourth generations, which had slightly increased in weight compared to the previous iPhones.
The two-gram weight difference in the disadvantage of the novel was really negligible.
But that's not the case with the new iPhones.
Compared with last year's iPhones, the smaller model weighed 14 grams, while the larger one weighed 20 grams.
On the one hand, it's no surprise that last year's Apple-in-the-pocket affair was a major blow to the company.
The new chassis is made of a more durable 7000 aluminium alloy, which also reflects on the weight.
But the displays have a much bigger impact on it.
Apple's new technology is 3D Touch, which lets the displays recognize the force of touch.
To do this, the display had to be fitted with an additional layer of capacitive sensors.
The new iPhones' displays have more than doubled in weight compared to previous generations.
The smaller iPhone went from 12 grams to 29 grams, and the larger iPhone went from 19 to 40 grams.
So, in the iPhone 6s, the screen is the heaviest component used.
The new model weighs only 143 grams, and this is achieved by the use of a degreasing crust that has touched most of the other components.
The battery is the heaviest component used on the larger model, but its weight has not changed from its predecessor.
Even here, the biggest increase is seen in the display.
The weight of the 5.5" iPhone 6s Plus is 192 grams.
How practical the new technology is for the display will be seen in the application.
The first users will be able to try it out on Friday, September 25th, when the iPhone 6s and 6s Plus go on sale in select countries.
