The windmill over Chlum is spinning again after years.
It can be seen from afar because it is placed on a fifteen-meter-high pole.
People in the area call it the "Clum Windmill".
For the municipality of 150 inhabitants, it even became one of the elements of the municipal emblem that the municipality received on the occasion of a gathering of locals in 2010.
"We asked for a sign and we wanted a fan on the sign, of course, everyone knows it in the area", said Mayor Jiří Mašek.
The Chlum windmill is a local engineering landmark.
It is also a bit of a modern day reminder of the times when people here fought for quality drinking water.
The one in Chlum in past centuries was a rarity.
It was not until 1910 that the Chlum representatives decided on a solution that was then suitable until the mid-1980s.
In the village near the Chichov branch, a well was dug 20 feet [7 m] deep.
