The manufacturer of the replica did not choose the right material and the wheel was not able to withstand strong winds.
Then the Chlum dominatrix lay undressed under the roof for several years.
But since June of this year, the wheel has been spinning on the high mast again.
On the occasion of a gathering of the villagers, the community had a replica of the wheel modified and reinstalled it on top of the iron tower.
But the wheel only pumps useful water from the well into the blind shoulder of the assailant.
And during the summer, we shut it down completely because the well was low on water.
At least it was empty.
"In the autumn, we will disconnect the windmill shaft from the pump in the suction basket again", explained Mayor Mašek.
Chlum is not the only municipality in the Czech Republic where the windmill has been registered as a municipal landmark, but it is the only one of its kind in the whole of the Highlands.
